    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-03-11T14:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-03-11T14:18:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>97. Notes on Telephone Conversation between <persName corresp="#p_KC_1"
                        >Kaysen</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName>, March
                        11<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d97fn1">Geneva discussion concerns. No
                        classification marking. 1 p. Kennedy Library, Ball Papers, Telephone
                        Conversations, Disarmament.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-03-11T14:18:00-05:00">March 11, 1962, 2:18 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d97-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d97-1"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Kaysen</persName> asked <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1"
                        >Ball</persName> if he had talked to Mac about the response to the Geneva
                    inquiry about the treaty. It seems to <persName corresp="#p_KC_1"
                        >Kaysen</persName> these fellows are trying to pull something. There is a
                    message from the President to the Secretary, <persName corresp="#p_FWC_1"
                        >Foster</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DA_1">Dean</persName> which
                    Beam and Boodby did. He told <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> he
                    might note also TOSEC 2 and TOSEC 6 to Geneva. They contain the President’s
                    policy line. After <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Kaysen</persName> talks to
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJE_1">Goodby</persName> and straightens him out he
                    will get back to <persName corresp="#p_BGW_1">Ball</persName> later.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
